- **Samata Sainik Dal**  ( __ Army of Soldiers for Equality __  [[2]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samata_Sainik_Dal#cite_note-2)  or  __ Party of the Fighters for Equality __  [[3]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samata_Sainik_Dal#cite_note-3) ) abbreviated as **SSD**  is a social organisation founded by [B. R. Ambedkar](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/B._R._Ambedkar)  on 24 September 1924 with the objective of safeguarding the rights of all oppressed sections of Indian society.[[4]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samata_Sainik_Dal#cite_note-4) [[5]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samata_Sainik_Dal#cite_note-Samata_Sainik_Dal_1936-5)  All India Equality Force
