- **Kalaram ** [**Temple**](https://drambedkarbooks.com/2016/03/02/2nd-march-1930-in-dalit-history-nashik-kalaram-temple-satyagraha-started/) ** entry movement ** formed a pivotal role in the [**Dalit**](https://www.ambedkaritetoday.com/category/caste-system) ** movement**  in India. B. K (Dadasaheb) Gaikwad and[**Dr. B. R. Ambedkar**](https://www.ambedkaritetoday.com//2019/04/about-dr-b-r-ambedkar-biography.html)  led a protest outside the temple on **2 March 1930** , in order to allowing [Dalits](https://www.ambedkaritetoday.com/2019/04/origin-of-untouchability-dalits-and.html)  into the temple.The movement was to have a** right to enter temple** , it was more towards having **equal rights** .
- We don’t want to go to temples though but we should have rights**Kala Ram Temple** is a beautiful temple in Old Nashik area, built by Sardar Rangarao Odhekar in 1788. Thousands of pilgrims visit the temple to take the blessings of Lord Ram.** But until 1930 no **[**dalit**](https://www.ambedkaritetoday.com/category/caste-system)** or **[**untouchable**](https://www.ambedkaritetoday.com/2019/04/origin-of-untouchability-dalits-and.html)** was allowed to enter the premises of the temple**. This was because of the rigid [caste system](https://www.ambedkaritetoday.com/category/caste-system) in India which prevails even today and is practiced since the Rigvedic period.
- It was because of the efforts of some prominent leaders like [Mahatma Jyotirao Phule](https://www.ambedkaritetoday.com//2019/04/about-jyotirao-phule-biography-life.html) the struggle for liberation of [Dalits](https://www.ambedkaritetoday.com/2019/04/origin-of-untouchability-dalits-and.html) was launched in India during the 19th century.After him it was [Dr. Babasaheb Ambedkar](https://www.ambedkaritetoday.com//2020/01/dr-br-ambedkar-the-man-and-his-message.html), a brilliant lawyer and was educated in United states with the help of scholarship given by Maharaja of Baroda, played a pivotal role in uplifting the [lower caste](https://www.ambedkaritetoday.com/category/caste-system) and fighting for their equal rights by late 1920s.
    - According to [Babasaheb](https://www.ambedkaritetoday.com/category/dr-ambedkar)  Ambedkar in order to break the wall between the upper class and lower caste it was important to get entry into temple because temples have been considered a place of origination of[caste annihilation](https://www.ambedkaritetoday.com//2019/05/the-annihilation-of-caste-speech-by-ambedkar.html) . Thus it became significant to break down the idea by entering the temple. For this movement , [**Kala Ram Temple**](https://studioaddablog.wordpress.com/2018/10/16/kala-ram-temple-satyagraha/)  was chosen.
    - It was this period when Civil Disobedience Movement was initiated by Mahatma Gandhi and thus Satyagraha prevailed in the country.**Dr. Ambedkar initiated Temple Entry Satyagraha**  after three months of painstaking and meticulous efforts in 1930. **It was one of the non violent movement where around 15000 people had participated to get entry into the temple. The Satyagrahis squatted before the temple, singing bhajans but a strong contingent of the Bombay police meted out the non violent Satyagrahis.**
    - **The Bombay police was supported by the orthodox Hindus. These people considered it as an unholy act. Because of this attitude of theirs harsh treatment was given not only to the satyagrahis but also to the untouchables of near by villages**. Their kids were expelled from the school, roads were closed for them, they were not allowed to buy articles of their daily needs from the local market. Despite this provocations, Dr. Babasaheb Ambedkar kept a check on his Satyagrahis and did not allow them to retaliate.
