- ^^**Indian Science Congress Association**^^
    - **Indian Science Congress Association** [[1]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_Science_Congress_Association#cite_note-1) (ISCA) is a premier scientific organisation of [India](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India)  with headquarters at [Kolkata](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kolkata) , [West Bengal](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_Bengal) . The association started in the year 1914 in [Kolkata](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kolkata)  and it meets annually in the first week of January. It has a membership of more than 30,000 scientists.
    - The first Indian Science Congress was held in 1914 at the [Asiatic Society](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Asiatic_Society)  in [Calcutta](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kolkata) . After [pseudoscientific speeches at the 2019 Indian Science Congress](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Indian_Science_Congress_pseudoscience_controversies) ,  the congress has established a policy that requires speakers at future  conferences to be vetted and scrutinizes the content of their talks.
    - 
- ^^**Asiatic Society**^^
    - **The Asiatic Society**  is an organisation founded during the [Company rule](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Company_rule_in_India)  in [India](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India)   to enhance and further the cause of "Oriental research", in this case,  research into India and the surrounding regions. It was founded by the  philologist [William Jones](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_Jones_(philologist) ) on 15 January 1784 in a meeting presided over by Justice [Robert Chambers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_Chambers_(English_judge) ) in [Calcutta](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calcutta) , the then capital of the British Raj.
    - At the time of its foundation, this Society was named as "**Asiatick Society** ". In 1825, the society was renamed as "The Asiatic Society". In 1832 the name was changed to "**The Asiatic Society of Bengal** " and again in 1936 it was renamed as "**The Royal Asiatic Society of Bengal** ". Finally, on 1 July 1951, the name of the society was changed to its present one. The Society is housed in a building at [Park Street](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Park_Street,_Kolkata)  in Kolkata (Calcutta). The Society moved into this building during 1808. In 1823, the [Medical and Physical Society of Calcutta](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medical_and_Physical_Society_of_Calcutta)  was formed and all the meetings of this society were held in the Asiatic Society.
